7 An Act relating to the Office of Juvenile Affairs;
making an appropriation; stating purpose; providing
8 an effective date; and declaring an emergency.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Office of
13 Juvenile Affairs from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
14 General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
15 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Two Hundred Fifty-two Thousand
16 Dollars ($252,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to
17 carry out the provisions of Enrolled House Bill No. 3755 of the 2nd
18 Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
20 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
21 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
22 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
23 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
24
